        -:  401:// Exponential function. Works by writing "x = m*log(2) + r" where
        -:  402:// "m = floor(x/log(2)+1/2)" and "r" is the remainder. The result is then
        -:  403:// "exp(x) = 2^m*exp(r)" where exp(r) is in the range [-1,1).
        -:  404:// exp(r) is computed using a 6th order minimax polynomial approximation.
        -:  405:template <typename Packet>
        -:  406:EIGEN_DEFINE_FUNCTION_ALLOWING_MULTIPLE_DEFINITIONS
